      {
        "text": "## Diagnosis: Auth Retry Loop Root Cause\n\nBased on the debug bundle and token file comparison:\n\n### The Problem\n\n**The retry loop fires because the agent is NOT reading `~/.openclaw/token.txt`** \u2014 it's pulling credentials from `openclaw.json` config instead, which has an OpenAI-format key that doesn't match the expected token format.\n\n### Token Prefix Comparison\n\n| Source | Token/API Key | Prefix |\n|--------|---------------|--------|\n| `~/.openclaw/token.txt` | `[REDACTED_TOKEN]` | `[REDACTED_TOKEN]` \u2705 |\n| `openclaw.json` config | `sk-n2ezsETTyUOjjS9...` | `sk-` \u274c |\n\n### Why the Loop Happens\n\n1. **Token prefix mismatch warning fires** \u2014 system expects `tok-*` format, gets `sk-*`\n2. **Retry loop starts** \u2014 but retries use the same config credentials (not re-reading token.txt)\n3. **Loop continues indefinitely** \u2014 same mismatched credentials = same failure\n\n### Local Credentials: NOT Stale\n\nThe `token.txt` prefix `[REDACTED_TOKEN]` is correct. The issue isn't stale credentials \u2014 **the agent simply isn't reading from token.txt**.\n\n---\n\n### Resolution Options\n\n1. **Fix credential source** \u2014 Ensure agent reads from `~/.openclaw/token.txt` for token validation, not `openclaw.json`\n2. **OR sync config** \u2014 Update the API key in `openclaw.json` to use the `tok-*` format token\n3. **Add guardrail** \u2014 Verify token read happens before auth retry to prevent infinite loops\n\nThe existing `INCIDENT-auth-retry-loop.md` already documents this \u2014 the fix just hasn't been applied yet.",
        "mediaUrl": null
      }
